"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The np.sinc function does not return 1 for input 0 and 0 for input 1. The np.sinc function returns sin(pi*x)/(pi*x) for x != 0 and 1 for x = 0. However, due to floating point precision issues, the result of np.sinc(1) is not exactly 0 but close to it.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7,8c7,8\\n< assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n< assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n> np.testing.assert_almost_equal(sinc_result[0], 1)\\n> np.testing.assert_almost_equal(sinc_result[1], np.sin(np.pi)/(np.pi))\"\n}"